5
[p 
	"After a while of making runs for Mega Man X games, I decided to make a Pokémon Gold run.
	$LF
	"This is due to both my interest in Pokémon, and the luck-manipulation and strategy part. For a
	$LF
	"while, Pokémon RB was a contested TAS, so I thought that it would be nice to try Pokémon Gold.
	$LF
	"Luck manipulation is never easy, but with enough determination, I am able to make the most
	$LF
	"unlikely events occur, although there aren't too many of them. The memory viewer is a
	$LF
	"big help in the making of this run.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"It was 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/Tilus 
		"Tilus
	]a
	"' 
	[a class=intlink href=/428M 
		"Pokémon Blue
	]a
	" run (later obsoleted, the most
	$LF
	"recent being 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/primorial#soup 
		"primorial#soup
	]a
	"'s 
	[a class=intlink href=/548M 
		"Pokémon Red
	]a
	" run) that inspired
	$LF
	"me to start
	$LF
	"looking at Pokémon Gold. Inspired by primorial#soup's naming convention, I use ! for the player,
	$LF
	"/ and - for Pokémon, and ??? for the rival. Just remember that when looking at the game script,
	$LF
	"so if you see !! or !?, it's referring to the player character.
	$LF
]p
